    <div id="Q120" class="question">
      <h4>120. What are the important CBA-related dates each season?</h4>

      <p>
        The following dates are referenced in the CBA, starting with July 1, which
        is the first day of the salary cap year. Any deadline which falls on a
        Saturday, Sunday or federal holiday is extended to the next business day.
      </p>

      <table class="nogrid"><tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>July 1</td>
          <td>Salary cap year begins</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td />
          <td>July Moratorium begins (see question number <a href="#Q105">105</a>)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td />
          <td>Salary cap adjusts (see question number <a href="#Q12">12</a>)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td />
          <td>Luxury tax threshold adjusts (see question number <a href="#Q18">18</a>)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td />
          <td>Salaries adjust</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td />
          <td>Exceptions arise (see question number <a href="#Q25">25</a>)</td>
        </tr>
